---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Methodology · State of AI Code Review"
  description="How the data was produced. Source, filters, implementation status definition, privacy thresholds, reproducibility, and the selection-bias correction applied between drafts."
  runningHead="Methodology"
  page="Methodology"
  theme="dark"
>

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="border-b border-night-50 bg-night-100">
    <div class="max-w-[1320px] mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 pt-16 md:pt-24 pb-16">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-8 items-start">
        <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-7">
          <div class="font-mono text-[12px] font-medium tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-phosphor-500 mb-5 reveal reveal-1">
            ◆ Apparatus
          </div>
          <h1 class="font-display leading-[0.98] tracking-tight text-mist-50 reveal reveal-2" style="font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 5rem);">
            How the <span class="italic phosphor">data was produced.</span>
          </h1>
        </div>
        <aside class="col-span-12 md:col-span-5 md:pt-6 reveal reveal-3">
          <div class="border-l border-night-50 pl-5">
            <p class="text-mist-200 leading-[1.6] text-[15px]">
              This section documents the dataset, filtering criteria, the definition of "implementation status," privacy thresholds, and the selection-bias correction that altered our acceptance numbers between internal drafts and publication.
            </p>
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SELECTION BIAS NOTE -->
  <section class="border-b border-night-50 bg-night-200">
    <div class="max-w-[1320px] mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 py-16">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-8 items-start">
        <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-3">
          <div class="font-mono text-[12px] font-medium tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-phosphor-500">A note on honesty</div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-9">
          <p class="font-display italic text-mist-50 leading-[1.3]" style="font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 2.6vw, 2.5rem);">
            An earlier internal draft reported 94.7% acceptance. That was wrong.
          </p>
          <p class="text-mist-200 leading-[1.7] text-[16px] mt-5 max-w-3xl">
            The draft counted only suggestions that received explicit developer feedback (thumbs-up, thumbs-down, or detected implementation). That table is a selection-biased subset of suggestions where the developer engaged. Silent ignores were missing entirely. When the full population is queried from the post-PR diff, the real implementation rate is 32%, not 94.7%. This report uses the full population.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-night-100">
    <div class="max-w-[1320px] mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 py-20">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-10 border-t border-night-50 pt-16">

        <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-3">
          <div class="font-mono text-[12px] font-medium tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-phosphor-500">§ i</div>
          <div class="font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-mist-200 mt-2">Source</div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-9">
          <p class="font-display italic text-mist-50 leading-[1.35]" style="font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 2.2vw, 2rem);">
            Production code reviews from the Kodus pipeline.
          </p>
          <p class="text-mist-200 leading-[1.7] mt-5 max-w-prose">
            Kodus reviews pull requests across GitHub, GitLab, Bitbucket, and Azure DevOps. The full dataset lives in a BigQuery warehouse. Each chart in this report has a backing SQL query published in the <a href="https://github.com/kodustech/stateofcodereview.com" class="phosphor underline decoration-1 underline-offset-4 hover:text-phosphor-300">GitHub repository</a> under <code class="font-mono text-sm bg-night-200 px-1.5 py-0.5 text-mist-50">methodology/queries/</code>.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="col-span-12 border-t border-night-50"></div>

        <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-3">
          <div class="font-mono text-[12px] font-medium tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-phosphor-500">§ ii</div>
          <div class="font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-mist-200 mt-2">Implementation status</div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-9">
          <p class="font-display italic text-mist-50 leading-[1.35]" style="font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 2.2vw, 2rem);">
            Measured from the post-PR diff, not opt-in feedback.
          </p>
          <p class="text-mist-200 leading-[1.7] mt-5 max-w-prose">
            For every delivered suggestion, the pipeline compares the suggested code against what actually shipped on those lines after the PR closed. The status is one of three:
          </p>
          <ul class="text-mist-200 leading-[1.75] mt-5 space-y-2 list-none max-w-prose">
            <li class="pl-7 relative"><span class="absolute left-0 top-0 font-mono phosphor">▣</span> <strong class="text-mist-50">implemented</strong> · the developer applied the suggested change closely.</li>
            <li class="pl-7 relative"><span class="absolute left-0 top-0 font-mono" style="color: var(--color-phosphor-300);">▦</span> <strong class="text-mist-50">partially_implemented</strong> · the developer changed those lines but not exactly as suggested. The idea was taken, the form was adapted.</li>
            <li class="pl-7 relative"><span class="absolute left-0 top-0 font-mono text-mist-400">▢</span> <strong class="text-mist-50">not_implemented</strong> · the lines were left untouched, or the change went in a different direction.</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-mist-200 leading-[1.7] mt-5 max-w-prose">
            This is a behavioral measure, not a quality measure. A correct suggestion ignored because the developer disagreed is counted as "not implemented." A wrong suggestion the developer happened to also fix differently is counted "partially."
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="col-span-12 border-t border-night-50"></div>

        <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-3">
          <div class="font-mono text-[12px] font-medium tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-phosphor-500">§ iii</div>
          <div class="font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-mist-200 mt-2">Scope</div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-9">
          <p class="font-display italic text-mist-50 leading-[1.35]" style="font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 2.2vw, 2rem);">
            Four canonical labels. Engine cutoff at 2025-09-01.
          </p>
          <p class="text-mist-200 leading-[1.7] mt-5 max-w-prose">
            The current engine emits four canonical labels: <strong class="text-mist-50">bug</strong>, <strong class="text-mist-50">security</strong>, <strong class="text-mist-50">performance</strong>, and <strong class="text-mist-50">kody_rules</strong> (team-authored review rules). Suggestions with deprecated labels (error_handling, potential_issues, maintainability, refactoring, documentation_and_comments, code_style, cross-file) are excluded — they came from earlier engine versions with different prompts and category boundaries.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="col-span-12 border-t border-night-50"></div>

        <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-3">
          <div class="font-mono text-[12px] font-medium tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-phosphor-500">§ iv</div>
          <div class="font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-mist-200 mt-2">Privacy</div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-9">
          <p class="font-display italic text-mist-50 leading-[1.35]" style="font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 2.2vw, 2rem);">
            Aggregation only.
          </p>
          <ul class="text-mist-200 leading-[1.75] mt-5 space-y-2 list-none max-w-prose">
            <li class="pl-7 relative"><span class="absolute left-0 top-0 font-mono phosphor">a.</span> No slice with fewer than 50 suggestions is published.</li>
            <li class="pl-7 relative"><span class="absolute left-0 top-0 font-mono phosphor">b.</span> Language slices with fewer than three distinct organizations are footnoted as low-confidence.</li>
            <li class="pl-7 relative"><span class="absolute left-0 top-0 font-mono phosphor">c.</span> Organization, repository, and pull-request identifiers are never exposed.</li>
            <li class="pl-7 relative"><span class="absolute left-0 top-0 font-mono phosphor">d.</span> Suggestion text shown in the report is reviewed for sensitive substrings before publication.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="col-span-12 border-t border-night-50"></div>

        <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-3">
          <div class="font-mono text-[12px] font-medium tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-phosphor-500">§ v</div>
          <div class="font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-mist-200 mt-2">Sample sizes · 2026-Q2</div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-9">
          <p class="font-display italic text-mist-50 leading-[1.35]" style="font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 2.2vw, 2rem);">
            2026-Q2 snapshot.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-6 border-t border-night-50">
            {[
              ['Delivered suggestions (sent, post-cutoff)', '162,262'],
              ['Distinct organizations', '464'],
              ['Fully implemented', '25,791 (15.9%)'],
              ['Partially implemented', '25,524 (15.7%)'],
              ['Any implementation', '51,315 (31.6%)'],
              ['Bug-label findings', '90,527'],
              ['Custom-rule findings (kody_rules)', '60,918'],
              ['Security findings', '6,552'],
              ['Performance findings', '4,265'],
              ['Organizations with BYOK config', '79'],
              ['LLM providers represented', '5'],
              ['Distinct models in production use', '20+'],
              ['Codified review rules (KodyRules)', '7,276'],
              ['Organizations with codified rules', '610'],
            ].map(([k, v]) => (
              <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between border-b border-night-50 py-2.5">
                <span class="text-mist-200">{k}</span>
                <span class="font-mono text-mist-50">{v}</span>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="col-span-12 border-t border-night-50"></div>

        <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-3">
          <div class="font-mono text-[12px] font-medium tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-phosphor-500">§ vi</div>
          <div class="font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-mist-200 mt-2">Out of scope</div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-9">
          <p class="font-display italic text-mist-50 leading-[1.35]" style="font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 2.2vw, 2rem);">
            What is not included.
          </p>
          <ul class="text-mist-200 leading-[1.75] mt-5 space-y-2 list-none max-w-prose">
            <li class="pl-7 relative"><span class="absolute left-0 top-0 font-mono phosphor">a.</span> Suggestions from Kodus self-hosted deployments. The data warehouse covers Cloud only.</li>
            <li class="pl-7 relative"><span class="absolute left-0 top-0 font-mono phosphor">b.</span> Suggestions where delivery failed (failed_lines_mismatch, failed). Excluded from rate denominators because they never reached the developer.</li>
            <li class="pl-7 relative"><span class="absolute left-0 top-0 font-mono phosphor">c.</span> Pull requests that never closed. Implementation status is only finalized at PR close.</li>
            <li class="pl-7 relative"><span class="absolute left-0 top-0 font-mono phosphor">d.</span> Pull requests from organizations that opted out of research. Reserved as policy. None currently.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="col-span-12 border-t border-night-50"></div>

        <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-3">
          <div class="font-mono text-[12px] font-medium tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-phosphor-500">§ vii</div>
          <div class="font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-mist-200 mt-2">Citation</div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-9">
          <p class="font-display italic text-mist-50 leading-[1.35]" style="font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 2.2vw, 2rem);">
            How to cite.
          </p>
          <pre class="font-mono text-sm bg-night-200 border-l-2 border-phosphor-500 p-5 leading-relaxed mt-6 max-w-prose text-mist-50">State of AI Code Review (2026-Q2).
Research by Kodus.
https://stateofcodereview.com</pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
